<h3>Banishment</h3>
<p>This spell will destroy a summoned being of level 46 or less outright.&nbsp;
This spell consumes a star ruby (roughly 70pp).&nbsp; Since the mob does get a
resistance save against this spell, it is a good idea to cast a debuff
first.&nbsp; Since this spell completely destroys the target, there is no
corpse, no experience and no message in the chat window.&nbsp; It's as if the
mob simply vanished.&nbsp; This spell has a 2 minute refresh time.&nbsp;
Although the 70pp per cast is reason enough not to chain cast it.</p>

<h3>Mala</h3>
<p>This is the final spell in the resist debuff line.&nbsp; Mala lowers resists
by 35 points, which is 25 less than the previous spell in the line.&nbsp;
However, mala cannot be resisted.&nbsp; The level 58 version, Malosini will
overwrite Mala.&nbsp; If you know a particular type of mob resists Malosini, try
Mala first and then cast Malosini again.&nbsp; Chances are, it will stick.&nbsp;
If you know a particular mob does not resist Malosini, you should just cast
Malosini on it.&nbsp; These two spells do not stack.</p>

<h3>Maelstrom of Electricity</h3>
<p>MoE is another of VI's odd spell offerings for magicians.&nbsp; It delivers
up to 3 waves of 675 damage for 475 mana (evoc-based).&nbsp; It checks
magic.&nbsp; What's odd about that?&nbsp; The level 59 Manastorm also delivers
up to 3 waves of damage (evoc) for only 427 mana -- further, it drains 50 mana a
wave from its target!&nbsp; Hmmm...</p>

<p>Some mages swear that MoE is resisted less than Manastorm, but nothing in the
spell data file seems to support that.&nbsp; I'd be interested in seeing logs
from other mages, but I say, "Myth!".</p>

<h3>Ancient Spells</h3>
<p>These are rare spells that drop only on Luclin bosses. At
this point, there are only 2 spells: Burnout V and Shock of the Sun (a
fire-based DD).&nbsp; I've seen discussions claiming the DD is unresistable.&nbsp;
From what I can see in the spell data file, that isn't true.  More myth?  Yep!</p>

<p><i>Historical Note: Due to a coding error, Ancient spells were dropping in
game for a short time on the wrong mobs.&nbsp; The error was fixed and those spells vanished from
spell books.&nbsp; They do drop, but only from the highest of Luclin mobs.&nbsp;
Many Luclin zone bosses drop 1 ancient (of any class) guaranteed.</i>

